# Pose Match — Project Context

You are working on **Pose Match**, a mobile AR app that takes a reference photo (typically a Pinterest pose) and overlays it onto a live camera feed, guiding both the subject and the photographer into the matching shot.

## The wedge

"I have THIS specific photo and I want THIS specific shot." Not generic pose suggestions — exact recreation. Keep this in mind for every product decision.

## Two failure modes the app must independently diagnose

1. **Subject guidance** — is the person in the right shape? (limb positions, head tilt, body orientation)
2. **Camera guidance** — is the lens in the right place? (framing, height, distance, angle)

## Tech stack (locked — do not deviate)

| Layer | Choice |
|---|---|
| Mobile framework | React Native + Expo bare workflow |
| Camera | react-native-vision-camera v4+ |
| On-device ML | MediaPipe Pose Landmarker (lite) via native bridge |
| Overlay rendering | @shopify/react-native-skia |
| Client state | Zustand + Reanimated shared values |
| Backend | Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Storage + Realtime) |
| Pose worker | Python (FastAPI + MediaPipe heavy) on Railway/Fly |
| Authz | Postgres RLS — no dedicated API server |
| Monorepo | pnpm workspaces |

## Where to find detail

- **Full architecture:** [architecture.md](mdc:architecture.md) — read before any structural decision
- **Build plan:** [tasks.md](mdc:tasks.md) — atomic, sequential tasks; complete one at a time

## Non-negotiables

- **ML and rendering run on-device.** Per-frame data never crosses the JS bridge.
- **No dedicated API server.** Mobile talks to Supabase directly; RLS handles authz; one Python worker handles reference keypoint extraction.
- **`pose-math` is pure TS, no native deps.** Used by both client (live matching) and worker (validation).
- **Three state tiers in mobile:** per-frame (Reanimated shared values), session (Zustand), persistent (Zustand + Supabase). Do not mix tiers.
- **The frame processor never calls React state.** Anything 30fps writes to a shared value.

## What's deliberately out of scope for v1

Scene/environment matching, multi-person poses, voice cues, social/sharing, web app, real-time multi-device collaboration. If a request touches these, flag as out-of-scope before building anything.

## Repo target structure

```
pose-match/
├── apps/mobile/             # React Native app (Expo bare)
├── services/pose-worker/    # Python keypoint extraction service
├── packages/
│   ├── pose-math/           # Pure TS comparison logic
│   └── shared-types/        # Shared TS types
└── supabase/
    ├── migrations/          # Postgres schema + RLS
    └── functions/           # Edge functions (Deno/TS)
```
